20/08/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Culture Minister Evangelos Venizelos told reporters on Tuesday (19 August) that his country was not under any immediate threat of terrorism. 
Pointing to a study by the British World Market Research Institute, he said that the government does not "have the feeling here that we are in a high danger zone". 
Venizelos went on to assure the public that Greek authorities, together with foreign agencies, are working hard to boost security for the 2004 Olympics. 
He was responding to criticism in the local media regarding Athens's readiness to hold the Summer Games. 
(AFP - 19/08/03)
